# G.O.S.T. TERMINAL Design Rules

When adding or modifying UI (modals, buttons, toggles, panels), follow the G.O.S.T. TERMINAL design system. Full spec: docs/DOCUMENTATION.md §4.4. Tokens: public/css/main.css (--gost-*).

## Colors
- Chassis bg: var(--gost-chassis) #1A1D1A
- Panel: var(--gost-panel) #2C302E
- Text: var(--gost-text) #E6E6E6
- Nominal/headers: var(--gost-nominal) #6E8B3D
- Active/selected: var(--gost-active) #DAA520
- Critical/destructive: var(--gost-critical) #A53A3A
- Bevel highlight: var(--gost-bevel-highlight) #7A7D7A
- Bevel shadow: var(--gost-bevel-shadow) #222422

## Flat Bevel
Buttons, tabs, panels: 2-3px border. Top/left = highlight, bottom/right = shadow. On :active, invert bevels and shift content 2px down/right. No border-radius.

## Forbidden
- Gradients, soft drop-shadows, smooth animations
- border-radius on panels/buttons
- Native switch components (use OFF [ ] ON mech-switch pattern)

## Typography
Headers/tabs: ALL CAPS. System IDs: [ BRACKETED ]. Sub-labels: Title Case. Font: chunky pixelated monospace.

## Mobile
Min touch target 48px vertical. 16px vertical gaps between zones. Edge-to-edge panels on mobile.
